'''''Almost Black: The True Story of How I Got Into Medical School By Pretending to Be Black''''' is a 2016 non-fiction book written by Vijay Jojo Chokal-Ingam, the brother of comedian [[Mindy Kaling]].<ref>[https://www.buzzfeed.com/stephaniemcneal/mindy-kalings-brother-says-he-got-into-medical-school BuzzFeed]</ref><ref>[http://www.people.com/article/mindy-kaling-brother-anti-affirmative-action-medical-school-application People.com]</ref><ref>[https://nypost.com/2015/04/05/mindy-kalings-brother-pretended-to-be-black-to-get-into-med-school/ New York Post]</ref><ref>[http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/mindy-kaling-distance-brother-race-claims-article-1.2175167 New York Daily News]</ref><ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/06/mindy-kaling-brother-posing-black-man-medical-school_n_7011720.html The Huffington Post]</ref><ref>[http://time.com/3771841/mindy-kalings-brother-claims-he-pretended-to-be-black-to-get-into-med-school/ Time]</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/booknews/11517877/Mindy-Kalings-brother-pretended-to-be-black-to-get-into-medical-school.html The Daily Telegraph]</ref><ref>[http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3026180/Mindy-Kaling-s-older-brother-claims-posed-black-man-medical-school.html The Daily Mail]</ref>
==Overview== The true story of how writer Vijay Jojo Chokal-Ingam, an [[Indian Americans|Indian American]], posed as an [[African Americans|African American]] in order to use [[affirmative action]] to get into medical school.
